│ <tool_call>           │
│ {                     │
│   "name":             │
│ <tool_name>,          │
│   "args": <tool_args> │
│ }                     │
│ </tool_call>          │
│                       │
│ For example:          │
│                       │
│ <tool_call>           │
│ {                     │
│   "name":             │
│ "get_weather",        │
│   "args": {           │
│     "location": "New  │
│ York",                │
│     "date":           │
│ "2023-10-01",         │
│     "celsius": true   │
│   }                   │
│ }                     │
│ </tool_call>          │
│                       │
│ ### Key Requirements  │
│ ###                   │
│                       │
│ 1. ALWAYS wrap your   │
│ response with         │
│ "<tool_call>" and     │
│ "</tool_call>" as     │
│ shown above so that I │
│ know you are calling  │
│ a tool.               │
│ 2. Content inside     │
│ "<tool_call>" and     │
│ "</tool_call>" MUST   │
│ be a valid JSON       │
│ object. Put all other │
│ content outside of    │
│ these tags.           │
│ 3. The "args" field   │
│ MUST also be a valid  │
│ JSON object. It is    │
│ NOT a string that     │
│ represents a JSON     │
│ object.               │
│ 4. Only call ONE tool │
│ in each of your       │
│ response. Do NOT call │
│ multiple tools at the │
│ same time.            │
│                       │
